            <fr:title text="Research">Research</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>My research interest spans from stochastic analysis, mathematical finance to category theory and mathematical logic. In particular, I focus on various approaches that postulate a clearer foundational framework for modern stochastic analysis. Some topics that I have been working on includes:</html:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:uri>https://sez.moe/0009/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>0009</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/0009/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Markov Category">Markov Category</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Markov category is a framework interpreting probability effects using <html:em>copy-discard categories</html:em>. Intuitively, a Markov category is a category where morphisms behave like “random functions”. This novel approach enables one to reason stocastic processes via string diagrams, similar to a relatively mature diagrammic intepretation on <fr:link href="/000D/" title="Quantum Processes" uri="https://sez.moe/000D/" display-uri="000D" type="local">quantum processes</fr:link>. A short yet clear survey can be found <fr:link href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Markov+category" type="external">here</fr:link>.</html:p>
                <html:p>I have written a set of note on Markov categories, which can be found <fr:link href="/000C/" title="Notes on Markov Categories" uri="https://sez.moe/000C/" display-uri="000C" type="local">here</fr:link>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
